modules.description: Parses Tailwind CSS selectors from a lexing buffer, handling syntax errors gracefully. Converts class names into utility-based CSS rules using internal mappings for variants and base styles. Processes input through a lexer to build structured representations of class combinations and their associated properties.

Processes Tailwind CSS class strings into optimized, expanded class lists by parsing and resolving utilities against internal variant and style mappings. It uses a lexer to convert class names into structured representations, handling syntax errors and supporting complex combinations of utilities and modifiers. The module operates on strings and hash tables to produce intermediate expressions used in subsequent compilation stages. This enables integration of Tailwind class transformation directly into OCaml-based JSX or templating workflows.
